f gangsters. This high moral, creeping prohibition is in effect encouraging the ever increasing growth of smuggling gangs. So in my mind lawlessness is being encouraged. So in the words of Tony Blair be tough on the crime and THE CAUSE'S OF CRIME which I think Westminster is the guilty party. Why criminalise people give them FREEDOM to smoke if that's what they want. Why moralise?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">I my opinion there is far </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt"> much of trying to tell people what they should be. Allow people to be themselves, after all this is supposed to be the land of the FREE.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Yours a concerned member of the public, who smokes and see's smuggling rife and accepted.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">Mr Terence E. Rowe</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">20 August 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>